											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/sarah-wild/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Sarah Wild is a freelance science journalist based in a sleepy village outside Canterbury in England. She’s written about exploding stars, microbes in the Namib Desert, and everything in between. Her work has appeared in <em>Nature</em>, <em>Science</em>, and <em>Scientific American</em>, among others.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/sarahwild-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/sarahwild-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/sarahwild-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/sarahwild-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/sarahwild-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/sarahwild.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
